metadata.description:
welcome to my debut sound.xyz drop.

if you like tom misch, cory wong, galantis, fred again.., great good fine okay, etc. there's something here for you.

'all right' incorporates a lot of musical elements that feel authentically me. intricate guitar parts, glitchy drums, lush chords. 

the lyrics are a blast of best wishes towards someone important in my life who has experienced and overcome an outsized amount of pain. it's a summer vibe that recognizes 

thank you for being here for my first ever solo drop on sound. the rest of this trip will 

*lyrics*

tonight i stopped by the bay
to wind up lost in the waves
reminds me of all the ways
you watch over me

time put space between us
and i've seen you break to pieces
but you're fearless facing
the years it's taking
to reset

light up what you got tonight 
and keep it glowing...
everyone you got at your side
i hope you hold them close to you...
might have been my night
but i woke up this morning...
trying to stay on my rise
just like you showed me how to do...

tonight i'm finally home
you're right to find your own
and i might be fine alone
just knowing you're all right

light up what you got tonight
and keep it glowing...
everyone you got at your side
i hope you hold them close to you...
might have been my night
but i woke up this morning...
trying to stay on my rise
just like you showed me how to do...

.b
